Hudson Street, west side, north from Jay Street, showing the U.S. Marine Hospital at the N.W. corner of Jay Street, and a portion of the Mercantile Exchange Building (with gabled roof) at the N.W. corner of Harrison Street.

October 10, 1927.

P. L. Sperr.

(1)

Hudson Street, west side, north from and including Jay, to and including Harrison Streets. Also shown (in foreground), is Worth Street, at, adjoining and east of the N.E. corner of Hudson Street. Notice the U.S. Marine Hospital No. 70, on the extreme left. Building with tower is the Mercantile Exchange.

August 20, 1928.

P. L. Sperr.

(2)

The same, another view. Excavation work seen in progress at the S.E. corner of Worth Street is for the new 24-story Western Union Building.

August 20, 1928.

P. L. Sperr.

(3)

The same, from a different angle.

August 20, 1928.

P. L. Sperr.
